{"key":"processedPost-10079426","value":{"id":10079426,"first":10079362,"last":10082917,"when":1238516274,"utime":"03/31/09 07:17 PM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br />- 4 inoculation points, holes are 7/32\"<br /></blockquote><br /><br />Holes are too big.&nbsp; That's providing fresh air exchange instead of gas exchange.<br /><br />Holes should be barely big enough for your inoculation needle to pass.&nbsp; I use 3/32\" holes, which is just under 1/8\"(Gawd, I'll be glad when the US finally goes metric). Yours are nearly 1/4\", and a 1/4\" hole is four times as large as a 1/8\" hole, thus one of yours are the size all four should be combined.&nbsp; Your substrate is drying out as it colonizes, and that's the number 1 pinning trigger.<br />RR","title":"Re: Avoiding early pinning in jars","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}